  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\nFor performance reasons we do verification of all signatures (except deposits) in a block as a single batch. If any of the signatures are invalid we just reject the block with \"Invalid signature\" but there's no way to tell which signature was invalid.  We should provide a `--X` option to both teku and the `teku transition blocks` subcommand (most importantly the transition subcommand) to identify exactly which signature is invalid and provide a more useful rejection message.\n\nOne way to do this would be to use a non-batching signature verifier though it will be slower.",
